<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="574" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,463,1138]" pageId="11" pageNumber="574">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1075,1101]" pageId="11" pageNumber="574">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is widely distributed in most parts of the Palaearctic Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Fontana, P. &amp; Buzzetti, F. M. &amp; Cogo, E. &amp; Ode, B." box="[1205,1432,1075,1102]" pageId="11" pageNumber="574" refId="ref8151" refString="Fontana, P., Buzzetti, F. M., Cogo, E. &amp; Ode, B. (2002) Guide to the recognition and study of grasshoppers, crickets, mantids and similar insects of Veneto: Blattaria, Mantodea, Isoptera, Orthoptera, Phasmatodea, Dermaptera, Embidiina. Archaeological Museum of Vicenza, Vicenza, 320 pp." type="book" year="2002">
Fontana 
<emphasis box="[1306,1364,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="574">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Willemse, L. P. M. &amp; Kleukers, R. &amp; Ode, B." box="[151,388,1111,1138]" pageId="11" pageNumber="574" refId="ref9306" refString="Willemse, L. P. M., Kleukers, R. &amp; Ode, B. (2018) The grasshoppers of Greece. Naturalis Biodiversity Center, Leiden, 440 pp." type="book" year="2018">
Willemse 
<emphasis box="[264,321,1111,1137]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="574">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
